possible to raise property or corporate taxes, a pattern now growing in the western states. Taxing the Poor demonstrates how sales taxes intended to replace the missing revenue—taxes that at first glance appear fair—actually punish the poor and exacerbate the very conditions that drove them into poverty in the first place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoorxTaxationzSouthern States. 0aPoorxTaxationzUnited States. 0aPovertyzSouthern States. 0aPovertyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aaccess to health care.  aafrican americans.  aamerican south.  aconsumers.  aconsumption.  acorporate taxes.  acrime.  aearly mortality.  aeconomics.  afood deserts.  ahealth care.  ahealth insurance.  ahigh school dropout.  aincome taxes.  alegislation.  amodern health care.  anonfiction.  aobesity.  apolitical science.  apoverty.  aprop 13.  aproperty taxes.  apublic education.  arace.  aracism.  aregressive sales tax.  arural.  asales tax.  asocial issues.  asocial policy.  asocial science.  astructural poverty.  ataxation.  ataxes.  ateen pregnancy.1 aLynch, Scott M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'Brien, Rourke, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026966840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094893840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948938/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY